//gravatar.com/avatar/2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f84ec51f9ceed468217d4e13abf78da9c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt","html_url":"https://github.com/jancborchardt","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-04-29t17:41:05z","updated_at":"2013-04-29t17:41:05z","body":"@lukasreschke any update on this btw?"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/17216080","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/1603#issuecomment-17216080","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1603","id":17216080,"user":{"login":"kaworu","id":109415,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/c14dadb0a6d5058d17b22c333998b9bc?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f5c90ea0e7bedb74b27852e5320d2e759.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"c14dadb0a6d5058d17b22c333998b9bc","url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu","html_url":"https://github.com/kaworu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kaworu/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-04-30t08:51:32z","updated_at":"2013-04-30t08:51:32z","body":"hi !\r\ni've landed here in my attempt to make owncloud play nice with fail2ban.\r\n\r\ni believe the patch has two issues in its current form:\r\n1. neither `checkblock()` nor `loginvalidattempt()` treat localhost as a special case. imho 127.0.0.1 and ::1 should never be blocked (this could be hardcoded or implemented by a configurable whitelist system).\r\n2. the localhost issue is common when owncloud is accessed through a localhost proxy. in that case, the \"real\" client's ip can be (usually) be found in the *x-forwarded-for* header while `$_server['remote_addr']` will contains the proxy's ip. the roundcube's ip logging function might be a good start: https://github.com/roundcube/roundcubemail/blob/master/program/lib/roundcube/rcube_utils.php#l644\r\n\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18022700","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/1603#issuecomment-18022700","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1603","id":18022700,"user":{"login":"bantu","id":189375,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/88483d87947219efecfc570465c753b2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fcdc48f189c0e2e8a870f3d54615a2f0d.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"88483d87947219efecfc570465c753b2","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu","html_url":"https://github.com/bantu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-16t19:13:46z","updated_at":"2013-05-16t19:13:46z","body":"a properly configured reverse proxy setup makes sure that owncloud gets the correct via remote_addr.\r\n\r\nif x-forwarded-for is to be supported it might make sense to have a whitelist of ips from which the x-forwarded-for headers are trusted (for all other sources, x-forwarded-for headers are thrown away)."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18024173","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/1603#issuecomment-18024173","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1603","id":18024173,"user":{"login":"bantu","id":189375,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/88483d87947219efecfc570465c753b2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fcdc48f189c0e2e8a870f3d54615a2f0d.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"88483d87947219efecfc570465c753b2","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu","html_url":"https://github.com/bantu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-16t19:39:57z","updated_at":"2013-05-16t19:40:25z","body":"i am not sure this patch is a good idea. it might create more problems than it solves:\r\n\r\nnats are used almost everywhere for mobile internet and some dsl providers are using it too because of ipv4 address exhaustion. universities are another good example.\r\n\r\nthis patch can be easily abused when behind a nat for a denial of service attack against all the other users behind the same nat. as long as you send login attempts fast enough, nobody else behind the same nat will be able to log in.\r\n\r\nalso, this patch does not work against brute force attacks via ipv6 because an attacker is likely able to freely pick a few bits of his ip address (usually ca. 64 bits).\r\n\r\nconsider the following instead:\r\n- after a certain number of tries, show a captcha to further slow down automated attacks. this likely won't do much because they usually can be cracked in seconds (or less) by non-php code.\r\n- increasing required password complexity to increase the search space an attacker has to search.\r\n\r\nand finally as a strategy consider\r\n- preferring user accounts with weak passwords being hacked instead of blocking users with good passwords from accessing their accounts.\r\n\r\ncc @karlitschek\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18024972","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/1603#issuecomment-18024972","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1603","id":18024972,"user":{"login":"lukasreschke","id":878997,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/f080e75d370a4d8e550983a4898bcf3b?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2ff12e47d5bb5359a9f58e8217413be790.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"f080e75d370a4d8e550983a4898bcf3b","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke","html_url":"https://github.com/lukasreschke","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-16t19:54:51z","updated_at":"2013-05-16t19:54:51z","body":"guys, this is a 3 month old pr which was written in about 10 - 20 minutes and is more of a proof of concept instead of a working solution. - i'm absolutely aware of the potential problems and am currently working on a proper two-factor authentication.\r\n\r\n(actually i have in mind to send the server response a little bit slower after every invalid login attempt to make bruteforcing more inefficient. - e.g. after 3 invalid logins there is a timeout of 10 seconds, after 5 a timeout of 20 seconds etc...)\r\n\r\n> nats are used almost everywhere for mobile internet and some dsl providers are using it too because of ipv4 address exhaustion.\r\n\r\ni'd blame the shitty provider here ;-)\r\n\r\n> as long as you send login attempts fast enough, nobody else behind the same nat will be able to log in.\r\n\r\ndude - you can easily dos a oc instance with an authenticated user account in two minutes. believe me, there are bigger issues an admin should care for at the moment ;-)\r\n\r\n> this patch can be easily abused when behind a nat for a denial of service attack against all the other users behind the same nat. as long as you send login attempts fast enough, nobody else behind the same nat will be able to log in.\r\n\r\nthat's why it will be configurable. - but the current login procedure is really more than insufficient.\r\n\r\n> also, this patch does not work against brute force attacks via ipv6 because an attacker is likely able to freely pick a few bits of his ip address (usually ca. 64 bits).\r\n\r\nack - but i hadn't had the time to implement this yet."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18025289","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/1603#issuecomment-18025289","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1603","id":18025289,"user":{"login":"lukasreschke","id":878997,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/f080e75d370a4d8e550983a4898bcf3b?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2ff12e47d5bb5359a9f58e8217413be790.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"f080e75d370a4d8e550983a4898bcf3b","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke","html_url":"https://github.com/lukasreschke","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukasreschke/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-16t20:00:18z","updated_at":"2013-05-16t20:00:18z","body":"don't understand me wrong - i'm *really* grateful for every comment here! i really believe that discussing security related code is the only way to ensure that it is adequate."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18025804","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/1603#issuecomment-18025804","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1603","id":18025804,"user":{"login":"bantu","id":189375,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/88483d87947219efecfc570465c753b2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fcdc48f189c0e2e8a870f3d54615a2f0d.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"88483d87947219efecfc570465c753b2","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu","html_url":"https://github.com/bantu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-16t20:09:29z","updated_at":"2013-05-16t20:17:38z","body":"> i'd blame the shitty provider here ;-)\r\n\r\nsounds like you perfectly understood the problem of ipv4 exhaustion there. ;-)\r\n\r\n> dude - you can easily dos a oc instance with an authenticated user account in two minutes. believe me, there are bigger issues an admin should care for at the moment ;-)\r\n\r\nwell, owncloud has to start somewhere with stopping making mistakes. :-p\r\n\r\n> don't understand me wrong - i'm really grateful for every comment here! i really believe that discussing security related code is the only way to ensure that it is adequate.\r\n\r\nyou're welcome. :)"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18828710","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/1603#issuecomment-18828710","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1603","id":18828710,"user":{"login":"ext-caucesystem","id":4255159,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/4921682665b99d47